deck: Metahuman team of prision guards.
description:
The Knight Shift was a team of metahumans guards who acted in behalf of Doctor 30. They were a group of mentally unstable subjects who developted sadism and cruelty against their fellow metahuman prisioners, depiste they also were prisioners in the past.

When Ferro returned to free his brother Douglas, he was captured by the Knight Shift, because Ingot joined the Knigth Shift. However, when he saw how the other members of the team threatened his brother, Douglas caused a riot among the prisioners who take revenge on the outnumbered guardians, leaving no survivors of the team.

The Knight Shift was a homage to the X-men in the same way as the Imperial Guard is a take on the Legion of Super-heroes.

Their membership beyond Dr 30 included X-men analogues: Taser (Cyclops); Psyche (Jean Grey); Landslide (Iceman); Fangg (Wolverine); Kritter (Beast). Douglas Nolan joined the team under the name Ingot (Colossus).
name: Knight Shift

Creation

name: The Five

deck: Created by Cadmus in the year 3000, the heroes from the past rise to fight the menaces of tomorrow.
description:
In an alternate dystopic future of the year 3000, Ariel Masters, a genetist from Cadmusworld created a process to recreate the legenday heroes from the 21st century. However to do that, they had to infect a host with the recovered DNA from another individual, this way killed the host organism and replaced him with a copy of the inoculated DNA source, including powers and memories. The process was far from perfect and the duplicates had gaps in their powers and memorieswhich were incomplete and distorted.

The result of the proyect was the birth of a new Justice League with the objetive to fight the Five, a group of powerful individuals who had taken over control of various galaxies. However, first the fragmented league must overcome their mutual desire to kill each other.

After a skirmish against the Five and the betrayal of Cadmus, the Justice League have retreat to the medieval world of Camelot 9, where they joined King Arthur forces against the Demon Etrigan. There they found themselves again with old friends as Ice and Fire, meanwhile on earth, Under disclosure circunstances, the League overcame the Kamelot 9 crisis and returned to Earth (Takron-Galtos), where the circunstances were far from different: now Firestorm controled Cadmus and the Commonwealth. The membership of the league were also altered with the inclusion of a female clone of Guy Gardner and Ice and Fire as permanent members. Later, Supergirl and a descendant of Batman also would join their shiftingmembership.

The league would had no time to deal with their unstable situation when the forces of Lady Styx, still alive in the future, attacked with her army of skullions. They demostrated their superiority killing effortlessly Superman and later Batman. The surviving member went into hidding awaiting fora chance to oppose to the total dominion of Lady Styx, who also conquered and destroyed Cadmusworld.

The League set their temporal headquarters in Themyscira, now an abandoned island, stil being pursued by the forces of Styx. Recently, they discovered than the skullions were really bodies used by the former member of the Five, the Convert. Also, unknown to them, they had been targeted by the royal guard of Lady Styx, the Legion of Death, leaded by Terry Magnus, who now owns the power of Eclipso.

Membership

The recreated members of the League are different from their previous incarnations.

  • Superman: He doesn't remember his life as Clark Kent. He haven't heat vision or fly powers. Instead, he can jump in a similar way to the golden age Superman. He has show romantic interest in the newest female Flash. He was killed by the Skullions.
  • Batman: He doesn't remember the killing of his parents neither any friendship with Superman. However he remembers his time with the Justice League International.
  • Wonder Woman: her warrior characteristics are more exacerbated. Less compassionated, she falls easly in berserker fury. She is also openly bisexual.
  • Flash 1 (Barry Allen "clone"): he hasn't an antifriction aura, so he uses an artificial one to prevent incineration. Barry was killed and resurrected three times before beign replaced by Teri.
  • Green Lantern (Hal Jordan"clone"): He has no ring, his energy comes from his body, but the use of his powers is killing him. Currently, he is reduced to 6 inch tall size
  • Green Lantern 2: (Guy Gardner in female form) Guy Gardner ressurrected as a woman. Ironically she still keeps the same personality.
  • Firestorm: Unstable recreation of the Firestorm Matrix than combines several Firestorm personalities. He left the team. Assumed the command of Cadmusworld, but was killed by Lady Styx forces.
  • Flash 2:(Teri Magnus "clone"): A mix of Teri Magnus and Barry Allen. She has show personality traits of Barry.
  • Tina Sung: Descendant of Bruce Wayne, she was an orphan of Takron Galtos who idolizes the legend of batman and ha her own archenemy in the form of a fan of Harley Quinn.
  • Supergirl: The original Supergirl from present time, just awakening from his escape capsule. The circunstances of her survival are unknown.

deck: The Cherokee Nation and Tribe
description:
The Cherokee are a Native American tribe who historically lived in the areas that would eventually become the states of Alabama, Georgia, North Carolina, South Carolina, and East Tennessee, later after the Trail of Tear in which the American Government uprooted them from their ancestral homes they settled mainly in Oklahoma.

The Cherokee speak an Iroquoian language that remains spoken today, and due to efforts of Sequoyah is the only such language with an alphabet and written language of its own.

The Cherokee have, like most other indigenous tribes in America, Canada and Mexico, been portrayed as individually and as a group in many comic books, almost always incorrectly. However there are also a number of notable comic book creators who have produced comic books and graphic novels of their own.
